      "content": "comforting how? like because there's no pressure to succeed? i guess. but it also feels like if the outcome is always the same, then there's no reason to endure the process. if everything is just going to end in nothingness, then the suffering feels totally unnecessary. doesn't it make sense that someone would just want to opt out of the struggle if there's nothing actually at stake?",
